726975f-a.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - New York Boulevard
726975f-a.text:
Jamaica Avenue, east from New York Boulevard, showing the
elevated structure of the B.M.T. subway system thereon and
Jamaica's business district. Next to the modernistic Eurts
Building is the Merrick Theatre and the Stuart Building. Across
the rooftops (left) is the First Presbyterian church steeple.
P. L. Sperr  April 1, 1932
NO REPRODUCTIONS

726976f-b.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - New York Boulevard
726976f-b.text:
Jamaica Avenue, at the S.W. corner of New York Boule-
vard, showing the former Van Wyck house, now occupied by
a drygoods store. The house was a Methodist Episcopal
church from 1873 to 1876 and was erected in 1846. The
owner of the structure in 1891 was J.B. Hopkins.
Views 1,2: 1922
View 3: 1923
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

727471f-b.title: Queens: New York Boulevard - Jamaica Avenue
727471f-b.text:
New York Boulevard, west side (former No. 32), between the
Long Island Railroad and Jamaica Ave., showing the Daniel Smith
residence of 1873;he erected the Town Hall of Jamaica. View
No. 2 shows a view of the upper floors of the house as seen from
the Long Island Railroad station.
1922.
View 21 May 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
